# <type>[optional scope]: <description>

# [optional body]

# [optional footer(s)]

# type can be e.g. <build|ci|docs|feat|fix|perf|refactor|test>
# scope can be the name of element/plugin.

# Description: Summary, imperative, start upper case, don't end with a period
# No more than 50 chars. #### 50 chars is here:  #

# blank line between title and body is required

# Body: Explain *what* and *why* (not *how*). Include link to issue.
# Wrap at 72 chars. ################################## which is here:  #

# a major version can be indicated with a '!' after the type/scope
# or with a BREAKING CHANGE trailer

# Examples

# ex.1
# feat: allow provided config object to extend other configs
#
# BREAKING CHANGE: `extends` key in config file is now used for extending other config files
# ex.2
# feat: allow provided config object to extend other configs
# ex.3
# feat(api)!: send an email to the customer when a product is shipped

# References:
# Conventional Commits
# https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/#summary
#
# How to Write a Git Commit Message:
# https://chris.beams.io/posts/git-commit/
